                    "value": "<p>A creature can provoke a waterlogged tiddalik into laughing and releasing its stored water with a successful DC 25 check to Perform a joke or funny story. The tiddalik also disgorges its water automatically if it dies while waterlogged, or can voluntarily Deluge as a three-action activity that has the concentrate trait.The mass of stored water swamps a 10-foot emanation, dealing [[/r 8d6 #bludgeoning]] bludgeoning damage to creatures in the area (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"25\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Deluge DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save) and making the area difficult terrain for 1 day. The tiddalik canâ€™t use its spit Strike or Expel Wave until it next Drinks in Abundance.</p>"
